Introduction to project
I would like to build a liquidity pool fund allocation system/tool that has a interface on telegram for this computing project, but before we get into the details, we need to understand the concept behind this system.
Breaking down – what is a Liquidity pool?
Firstly, a liquidity pool in this case is one of the most important aspects of decentralised Web3 and blockchain technology, a liquidity pool is like the Jerusalem of decentralised crypto trading and development.
So what actually is a liquidity pool (LP)?
A liquidity pool, or (LP), is basically a smart contract that holds two different crypto tokens in a pair , for example, ETH and USDT can be held in a that pool uses these two assets to let people swap one for the other at any time, without needing a middleman or traditional order book like in Binance , Coinbase or many other traditional exchanges.
So instead of matching buyers and sellers, the LP is always ready to trade with you directly , and when you put in ETH and want USDT, the LP calculates the price using a special formula (normally something like xy=k*) and gives you the USDT. The ETH you give in goes into the pool, and the USDT comes out.
As people trade, the price shifts automatically, based on supply of the 2 tokens, as one token is demanded more the other one will be used to swap so there will be more of one token and less of the other. This is why prices can change rapidly, it’s all happening inside the pool.
And finally the core of this project is aiming at People (called liquidity providers) put money into the pool and in return earn a cut of the trading fees. These fees are what drives people to provide liquidity in these pools and earn a profit.
Investing in a LP pool allows the investor to take 50% less risk and make 50% less profit in that specific trading pair due to it’s mechanisms, in more recent developments a price range could be set for a pair of LP which allows more control for the investor and is one of the key features this project will integrate.


The issue
The stakeholder for this project is an experienced crypto investor who is confident in DeFi and liquidity provisioning but finds it difficult to efficiently manage their capital without constantly monitoring market conditions. They explained that one of their main challenges is accurately matching their investment size to the level of opportunity available — without taking on more risk than they are comfortable with.
Although they understand the potential of liquidity pools (LPs), the current manual process of checking platforms like Uniswap or PancakeSwap, comparing pool returns, managing risk exposure, and rebalancing investments is too time-consuming and impractical. For someone who wants to stay on top of fast-moving opportunities but doesn’t have time to check multiple dashboards every few hours, this leads to inefficiencies and missed returns.
They also pointed out the lack of a tool that can simulate potential profit and risk outcomes before investing. At present, most tools focus only on displaying real-time APYs and liquidity data — they don’t help users decide how much to invest, where, or why based on the user’s goals.
This project addresses those pain points by providing the stakeholder with a Telegram-based bot that:
•	Automatically tracks high-yield liquidity pools,
•	Categorises pools by volatility level,
•	Allocates capital intelligently based on risk-reward ratio,
•	Simulates potential outcomes,
•	Adjusts positions without the user needing to constantly intervene.
The system is designed to save the stakeholder time, reduce cognitive load, and help them maintain a more balanced and consistent return — without the need for constant manual oversight.


